The Catalog sales objective also includes additional creative optimizations via Performance+ creative.\n\nFeatures\n\nPerformance+ combines Pinterest\u2019s top performing automation and AI features into a simplified campaign setup with 50% fewer inputs and optimized features:\n\n* Simple activation: Activate Performance+ campaigns with a toggle at the beginning of campaign creation for Consideration, Conversions or Catalog sales campaigns.\n* Ad groups: A new ad group is automatically created when you begin a new Performance+ campaign.\u00a0\n* Budget: Performance+ uses Lifetime and Average Daily budgets only. There\u2019s no budget limit per campaign.\n* Performance+ creative for the Catalog sales objective: You have the option to use AI to generate image backgrounds, and/or implement creative optimizations which automatically create Collections and Shopping ads from your catalog.\n* Targeting: Simplified targeting options to maximize performance. Performance+ campaigns allow country picker, simplified age targeting, and support Customer lists (include / exclude).\u00a0\n* Optimization &amp; Delivery:\n\n  * Performance+ campaigns use Performance+ bidding to ensure the most outcomes for the lowest cost.\n  * Conversion and Catalog Sales campaigns can use conversions and add to cart as conversion events.\u00a0\n\n* Catalog Sales Product Groups: Performance+ uses the All Products product group and does not include a Product Group picker.\n\nAd groups\n\nPerformance+ automatically creates ad groups for your campaigns based on different actions taken during the create flow process.\u00a0\n\n* All Performance+ campaigns automatically receive one auto generated ad group\u00a0\n* If you include a customer list in your campaign, we\u2019ll create a second remarketing ad group from your customer list(s).\u00a0\n* If you run a Performance+ Catalog sales campaign we\u2019ll create a prospecting ad group (using the All Products product group) and another Dynamic Retargeting ad group to remarket to users. \u00a0You can not opt out of the Dynamic Retargeting ad group during the create flow experience, nor can you control the percentage of spend that goes to each ad group.\u00a0\n* If you add a customer list to your Performance+ Catalog sales campaign we\u2019ll also make a third ad group targeting those users.\n\nPerformance+ creative\n\nPerformance+ creative provides automated assistance to help you create ads across multiple Pinterest formats, optimize your ads according to your campaign objectives and use AI to generate backgrounds for both Performance+ and non-Performance+ Catalog sales campaigns.\n\n* Creative optimizations: Automatically turn your product Pins into multiple types of ads (collections and shopping) and deliver the best performing ads to users at scale.\n* Generate backgrounds: Uses generative AI to apply backgrounds for your product images that help drive user inspiration and engagement.\n\nPerformance+ creative is available for both Performance+ and non-Performance+ Catalog sales campaigns.\n\nNote: Generate backgrounds and Creative optimizations can be used independently or together.\n\nPerformance+ setup\n\nLearning mode\n\nAfter launching a Performance+ campaign advertisers will see an icon on the Ads Reporting dashboard for Learning that indicates that your campaign is new and still finding the right audience.\n\nOnce you create a campaign, we show the ads to different types of people to learn who is most likely to convert. During this phase, your campaign may experience some performance fluctuations.\n\nOnce Learning mode is complete and we have enough data, we show your ads to the people most likely to convert. At this point, your campaign\u2019s performance should stabilize and you can make changes. If you make changes to your campaign while it\u2019s in Learning mode, it might reset and take longer.\n\nDon\u2019t turn off your campaign during Learning Mode, and wait for the Learning indicator to disappear so that we can deliver the best results.\n\nLearning mode varies by each unique advertiser with no set time horizon for when it will turn off. Learning mode is removed when the system finds that conversion events have stabilized. The removal of the Learning indicator takes on average two weeks, but may vary depending on factors such as campaign spend, conversion events on your site, engagement with your ads, and more.\n\nYou\u2019ll get the best idea of true campaign performance if you assess your Performance+ campaigns weekly or monthly rather than daily.  \n\n* Log in to your Pinterest business account \n* Click Business hub at the top-left corner of your screen \n* Click Create campaign \n* Select Manual campaign, then click Get started \n* Select Consideration as the campaign objective \n* Click the Performance+ On toggle to activate the Performance+ simplified campaign mode \n* Fill in your Campaign name and Campaign status \n* Choose your Campaign budget and schedule. \u00a0Performance+ campaigns only allow Lifetime and flexible daily budgets.\n* Enter your targeting details. Performance+ campaigns only allow additional targeting by Country, Age and Customer lists.\n* Performance+ uses automatic bidding for campaign delivery.\u00a0\n* Select the Pins for your ads \n* Once you\u2019ve entered all the details, click Publish\n\n* Log in to your Pinterest business account \n* Click Business hub at the top-left corner of your screen \n* Click Create campaign \n* Select Manual campaign, then click Get started \n* Select Conversions as the campaign objective \n* Click the Performance+ On toggle to activate the Performance+ simplified campaign mode \n* Fill in your Campaign name and Campaign status \n* Choose your Campaign budget and schedule. \u00a0Performance+ campaigns only allow Lifetime and flexible daily budgets.\n* Enter your targeting details. Performance+ campaigns only allow additional targeting by Country, Age and Customer lists.\n* Enter your conversion data and conversion event. Performance+ only supports Conversion and Add to cart as conversion events.\u00a0\n* Select the Pins for your ads \n* Once you\u2019ve entered all the details, click Publish\n\n* Log in to your Pinterest business account \n* Click Business hub at the top-left corner of your screen \n* Click Create campaign \n* Select Manual campaign, then click Get started \n* Select Catalog sales as the campaign objective \n* Click the Performance+ On toggle to activate the Performance+ simplified campaign mode \n* Fill in your Campaign name and Campaign status \n* Choose your Campaign budget and schedule. \u00a0Performance+ campaigns only allow Lifetime and flexible daily budgets \n* Fill in your Product group information. Select your product feed\u00a0\n\n  1. Click the Creative optimizations toggle to automatically turn your product Pins into multiple types of ads (collections and shopping)\u00a0\n  2. Click the Generate backgrounds toggle to create backgrounds for your eligible product images. Turning on the Generate backgrounds feature will not update the ad preview window.\n\n* Enter your targeting details. Performance+ campaigns only allow additional targeting by Country, Age and Customer lists.\n* Choose your Optimization strategy. Enter your conversion data and conversion event. Performance+ only supports Conversion and Add to cart as conversion events.\n* Once you\u2019ve entered all the details, click Publish.\n\nCreative optimizations automatically turn your product Pins into multiple types of ads (collections and shopping) to help deliver the best performing ads to users. You can use creative optimizations in any Catalog sales campaign, independent of the other Performance+ features.\u00a0\n\n* Log in to your Pinterest business account \n* Click Business hub at the top-left corner of your screen \n* Click Create campaign \n* Select Manual campaign, then click Get started \n* Select Catalog sales (either Performance+ or non-Performance+) as the campaign objective \n* Fill in the rest of the details, then click Continue\n\n  1. For non-Performance+ campaigns, choose one or more product groups\n\n* Toggle on Creative optimizations in the top-right corner \n* Once you\u2019ve entered all the details, click Publish  \n\nPerformance+ creative uses generative AI to apply backgrounds for your product images that help drive user inspiration and engagement.\n\nYou can use the generated backgrounds feature in any Catalog sales campaign, independent of the other Performance+ features. Generated backgrounds are only available for eligible product images.\n\n* Log in to your Pinterest business account \n* Click Business hub at the top-left corner of your screen \n* Click Create campaign \n* Select Manual campaign, then click Get started \n* Select Catalog sales (either Performance+ or non-Performance+) as the campaign objective \n* Fill in the rest of the details, then click Continue\n\n  1. For non-Performance+ campaigns, choose one or more product groups\n\n* At the right-side of the screen, toggle on Generate backgrounds. Turning on the Generate backgrounds feature will not update the ad preview window.\u00a0\n* To preview sample backgrounds, click View sample \n* Once you\u2019ve entered all the details, click Publish\n\nNote:\n\n* We may change the image aspect ratio to fit our ad guidelines.\u00a0\n* We may add backgrounds to product images that range from complex lifestyle scenes to simple colors.\u00a0\n* If any logos or overlays are a part of the background we may remove them in order to apply the generated background.  \n\nPerformance+ campaign reporting\u00a0\n\nAdvertisers will see your traditional metrics on the Ads manager Ads reporting page with some changes to the targeting breakdown feature.\n\nYou can choose to see targeting breakdowns by ad groups, geography and audience list, if a list was included. Advertiser cannot access the targeting breakdowns in Performance+ campaigns for:\u00a0\n\n* Gender\u00a0\n* Age\u00a0\n* Language\u00a0\n* Interests\u00a0\n* Keywords\u00a0\n* Device\u00a0\n* Placement\nPerformance+ creative reporting\n\nIf you\u2019re using either creative optimizations or generated backgrounds in your Catalog sales campaigns, you can view information about these features in Ads Manager.\n\n* Log in to your Pinterest business account \n* Click Business hub at the top-left corner of your screen \n* Click Ad reporting \n* To see reporting for creative optimizations: \n\n  1. Click the Product groups tab\u00a0\n  2. Creative optimizations are listed in the Product group ad format column\n\n* To see reporting for generated backgrounds:\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\n\n  1. Click Custom reports.\n  2. Click Create new report\n  3. Select the Product Group level\n  4. Click Targeting breakdown and select Generated backgrounds\n  5. Once you\u2019ve entered all the details, click Run report or Run and save  \n\nOptimization Guidelines\u00a0 Set your Performance+ campaigns up for success\n* Accurately track your conversions Integrate the Pinterest Conversions API and/or the Pinterest Tag for accurate conversion tracking.\n* Make a meaningful investment with sufficient conversion volume Allocate a sufficient budget \u00a0to scale impressions and find the right users. We recommend an investment 5 times above your cost per acquisition goal.\u00a0\n* Provide a variety of creative We recommend at least 10 ads per ad group, but more is better so we can find the best performers and serve them more often.\u00a0\n\n  * Remove under performing creative from Ad Groups to improve performance, and add additional creative to ensure the system can optimize to the top performers. Note: wait until Learning mode has ended before pausing or adding more Creative to an Ad Group.\u00a0\n  * If you\u2019re running Performance+ Catalog sales campaigns, we recommend using Performance+ creative to apply generated backgrounds and/or creative optimizations to automatically create thousands of Shopping and Collections ads from your catalog.\n\nAllocating spend for your Performance+ test\n\n* Set your objective based on scale Performance+ Conversions and Catalog sales campaigns perform best with 50+ conversion events per week. \n\n  * Over 50 weekly conversions: Launch a Performance+ Conversion or Performance+ Catalog Sales campaign to drive performance.\n  * Under 50 weekly conversions: Start with Performance+ Consideration objective to drive interest in your brand/product and increase conversion events on the site.\u00a0\n\n* Know your Cost Per Action goals If you evaluate campaign performance on a Cost Per Action (CPA) goal, your daily budget should be at least 5x your cost per result goal.\n* Optimize your campaign Gradually increase your budget by 20\u201330% based on performance.\nThe Performance+ campaign optimization cycle\n\nPerformance+ campaigns cycle from learning mode, to making optimizations, back to learning mode so our advertising technology can help drive the best results.\n\nTo optimize your campaigns:\n\n* Launch your campaign \n* Wait for learning mode to finish \n* Pause underperforming ads \n* Add fresh ads \n* Repeat.\n\nMaking changes while the Learning indicator is showing can disrupt this cycle. Instead, wait for the Learning indicator to disappear before making any changes to ads or budget. The removal of the Learning indicator takes on average two weeks, but may vary depending on factors such as campaign spend, conversion events on your site, engagement with your ads, and more.\n\nDriving results with creative refreshes\n\n* Test and evaluate your creative\u00a0\n\n  * Test various landing pages (product, category, homepage).\n  * Review bounce rates by format and creative.\u00a0\n  * Test mobile deep links vs. non-mobile deep links if applicable.\n  * Experiment with different text overlay CTAs.\n\n* Pause underperforming pins Pause any Pins below campaign KPIs, and keep only creative that meets performance goals. Note: Do not pause ads during Learning mode.\u00a0\n* Launch new creative After pausing low performers, add at least 10 new creatives per Ad Group. Test different formats and landing pages to continue improving. \n\n  * If you\u2019re running Performance+ Catalog sales campaigns, we recommend using Performance+ creative to apply generated backgrounds and/or creative optimizations to automatically create thousands of Shopping and Collections ads from your catalog.  \n\n End of Other articles Links \n\nStill need help? The Catalog sales objective also includes additional creative optimizations via Performance+ creative.\n\nFeatures\n\nPerformance+ combines Pinterest\u2019s top performing automation and AI features into a simplified campaign setup with 50% fewer inputs and optimized features:\n\n* Simple activation: Activate Performance+ campaigns with a toggle at the beginning of campaign creation for Consideration, Conversions or Catalog sales campaigns.\n* Ad groups: A new ad group is automatically created when you begin a new Performance+ campaign.\u00a0\n* Budget: Performance+ uses Lifetime and Average Daily budgets only. There\u2019s no budget limit per campaign.\n* Performance+ creative for the Catalog sales objective: You have the option to use AI to generate image backgrounds, and/or implement creative optimizations which automatically create Collections and Shopping ads from your catalog.\n* Targeting: Simplified targeting options to maximize performance. Performance+ campaigns allow country picker, simplified age targeting, and support Customer lists (include / exclude).\u00a0\n* Optimization &amp; Delivery:\n\n  * Performance+ campaigns use Performance+ bidding to ensure the most outcomes for the lowest cost.\n  * Conversion and Catalog Sales campaigns can use conversions and add to cart as conversion events.\u00a0\n\n* Catalog Sales Product Groups: Performance+ uses the All Products product group and does not include a Product Group picker.\n\nAd groups\n\nPerformance+ automatically creates ad groups for your campaigns based on different actions taken during the create flow process.\u00a0\n\n* All Performance+ campaigns automatically receive one auto generated ad group\u00a0\n* If you include a customer list in your campaign, we\u2019ll create a second remarketing ad group from your customer list(s).\u00a0\n* If you run a Performance+ Catalog sales campaign we\u2019ll create a prospecting ad group (using the All Products product group) and another Dynamic Retargeting ad group to remarket to users. \u00a0You can not opt out of the Dynamic Retargeting ad group during the create flow experience, nor can you control the percentage of spend that goes to each ad group.\u00a0\n* If you add a customer list to your Performance+ Catalog sales campaign we\u2019ll also make a third ad group targeting those users.\n\nPerformance+ creative\n\nPerformance+ creative provides automated assistance to help you create ads across multiple Pinterest formats, optimize your ads according to your campaign objectives and use AI to generate backgrounds for both Performance+ and non-Performance+ Catalog sales campaigns.\n\n* Creative optimizations: Automatically turn your product Pins into multiple types of ads (collections and shopping) and deliver the best performing ads to users at scale.\n* Generate backgrounds: Uses generative AI to apply backgrounds for your product images that help drive user inspiration and engagement.\n\nPerformance+ creative is available for both Performance+ and non-Performance+ Catalog sales campaigns.\n\nNote: Generate backgrounds and Creative optimizations can be used independently or together.\n\nPerformance+ setup\n\nLearning mode\n\nAfter launching a Performance+ campaign advertisers will see an icon on the Ads Reporting dashboard for Learning that indicates that your campaign is new and still finding the right audience.\n\nOnce you create a campaign, we show the ads to different types of people to learn who is most likely to convert. During this phase, your campaign may experience some performance fluctuations.\n\nOnce Learning mode is complete and we have enough data, we show your ads to the people most likely to convert. At this point, your campaign\u2019s performance should stabilize and you can make changes. If you make changes to your campaign while it\u2019s in Learning mode, it might reset and take longer.\n\nDon\u2019t turn off your campaign during Learning Mode, and wait for the Learning indicator to disappear so that we can deliver the best results.\n\nLearning mode varies by each unique advertiser with no set time horizon for when it will turn off. Learning mode is removed when the system finds that conversion events have stabilized. The removal of the Learning indicator takes on average two weeks, but may vary depending on factors such as campaign spend, conversion events on your site, engagement with your ads, and more.\n\nYou\u2019ll get the best idea of true campaign performance if you assess your Performance+ campaigns weekly or monthly rather than daily.  \n\n* Log in to your Pinterest business account \n* Click Business hub at the top-left corner of your screen \n* Click Create campaign \n* Select Manual campaign, then click Get started \n* Select Consideration as the campaign objective \n* Click the Performance+ On toggle to activate the Performance+ simplified campaign mode \n* Fill in your Campaign name and Campaign status \n* Choose your Campaign budget and schedule. \u00a0Performance+ campaigns only allow Lifetime and flexible daily budgets.\n* Enter your targeting details. Performance+ campaigns only allow additional targeting by Country, Age and Customer lists.\n* Performance+ uses automatic bidding for campaign delivery.\u00a0\n* Select the Pins for your ads \n* Once you\u2019ve entered all the details, click Publish\n\n* Log in to your Pinterest business account \n* Click Business hub at the top-left corner of your screen \n* Click Create campaign \n* Select Manual campaign, then click Get started \n* Select Conversions as the campaign objective \n* Click the Performance+ On toggle to activate the Performance+ simplified campaign mode \n* Fill in your Campaign name and Campaign status \n* Choose your Campaign budget and schedule. \u00a0Performance+ campaigns only allow Lifetime and flexible daily budgets.\n* Enter your targeting details. Performance+ campaigns only allow additional targeting by Country, Age and Customer lists.\n* Enter your conversion data and conversion event. Performance+ only supports Conversion and Add to cart as conversion events.\u00a0\n* Select the Pins for your ads \n* Once you\u2019ve entered all the details, click Publish\n\n* Log in to your Pinterest business account \n* Click Business hub at the top-left corner of your screen \n* Click Create campaign \n* Select Manual campaign, then click Get started \n* Select Catalog sales as the campaign objective \n* Click the Performance+ On toggle to activate the Performance+ simplified campaign mode \n* Fill in your Campaign name and Campaign status \n* Choose your Campaign budget and schedule. \u00a0Performance+ campaigns only allow Lifetime and flexible daily budgets \n* Fill in your Product group information. Select your product feed\u00a0\n\n  1. Click the Creative optimizations toggle to automatically turn your product Pins into multiple types of ads (collections and shopping)\u00a0\n  2. Click the Generate backgrounds toggle to create backgrounds for your eligible product images. Turning on the Generate backgrounds feature will not update the ad preview window.\n\n* Enter your targeting details. Performance+ campaigns only allow additional targeting by Country, Age and Customer lists.\n* Choose your Optimization strategy. Enter your conversion data and conversion event. Performance+ only supports Conversion and Add to cart as conversion events.\n* Once you\u2019ve entered all the details, click Publish.\n\nCreative optimizations automatically turn your product Pins into multiple types of ads (collections and shopping) to help deliver the best performing ads to users. You can use creative optimizations in any Catalog sales campaign, independent of the other Performance+ features.\u00a0\n\n* Log in to your Pinterest business account \n* Click Business hub at the top-left corner of your screen \n* Click Create campaign \n* Select Manual campaign, then click Get started \n* Select Catalog sales (either Performance+ or non-Performance+) as the campaign objective \n* Fill in the rest of the details, then click Continue\n\n  1. For non-Performance+ campaigns, choose one or more product groups\n\n* Toggle on Creative optimizations in the top-right corner \n* Once you\u2019ve entered all the details, click Publish  \n\nPerformance+ creative uses generative AI to apply backgrounds for your product images that help drive user inspiration and engagement.\n\nYou can use the generated backgrounds feature in any Catalog sales campaign, independent of the other Performance+ features. Generated backgrounds are only available for eligible product images.\n\n* Log in to your Pinterest business account \n* Click Business hub at the top-left corner of your screen \n* Click Create campaign \n* Select Manual campaign, then click Get started \n* Select Catalog sales (either Performance+ or non-Performance+) as the campaign objective \n* Fill in the rest of the details, then click Continue\n\n  1. For non-Performance+ campaigns, choose one or more product groups\n\n* At the right-side of the screen, toggle on Generate backgrounds. Turning on the Generate backgrounds feature will not update the ad preview window.\u00a0\n* To preview sample backgrounds, click View sample \n* Once you\u2019ve entered all the details, click Publish\n\nNote:\n\n* We may change the image aspect ratio to fit our ad guidelines.\u00a0\n* We may add backgrounds to product images that range from complex lifestyle scenes to simple colors.\u00a0\n* If any logos or overlays are a part of the background we may remove them in order to apply the generated background.  \n\nPerformance+ campaign reporting\u00a0\n\nAdvertisers will see your traditional metrics on the Ads manager Ads reporting page with some changes to the targeting breakdown feature.\n\nYou can choose to see targeting breakdowns by ad groups, geography and audience list, if a list was included. Advertiser cannot access the targeting breakdowns in Performance+ campaigns for:\u00a0\n\n* Gender\u00a0\n* Age\u00a0\n* Language\u00a0\n* Interests\u00a0\n* Keywords\u00a0\n* Device\u00a0\n* Placement\nPerformance+ creative reporting\n\nIf you\u2019re using either creative optimizations or generated backgrounds in your Catalog sales campaigns, you can view information about these features in Ads Manager.\n\n* Log in to your Pinterest business account \n* Click Business hub at the top-left corner of your screen \n* Click Ad reporting \n* To see reporting for creative optimizations: \n\n  1. Click the Product groups tab\u00a0\n  2. Creative optimizations are listed in the Product group ad format column\n\n* To see reporting for generated backgrounds:\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\n\n  1. Click Custom reports.\n  2. Click Create new report\n  3. Select the Product Group level\n  4. Click Targeting breakdown and select Generated backgrounds\n  5. Once you\u2019ve entered all the details, click Run report or Run and save  \n\nOptimization Guidelines\u00a0 Set your Performance+ campaigns up for success\n* Accurately track your conversions Integrate the Pinterest Conversions API and/or the Pinterest Tag for accurate conversion tracking.\n* Make a meaningful investment with sufficient conversion volume Allocate a sufficient budget \u00a0to scale impressions and find the right users. This website seems to offer content and possible also services in this area. Please make sure you are not investing in a scam. Check our article on \u301031\u2020How to check if a forex or investment site is legit or a scam?\u3011.\n\nThis website, which appears to provide banking, money lending, stock trading, and other financial services, is hosted on a shared server. An attacker might use one compromised website on the same server as a portal to all other websites on the same server if you employ a shared server for such data-sensitive services. We advise you to think twice about using this website&#x27;s services because the personal information you enter on it, and consequently, your device, could be hacked.\n\n### Webshop Review\n\nThe Tranco ranking of this website is low. This can be considered low in relation to other websites from the website&#x27;s country. If you think this website should be very popular, please invest additional time in researching the company as this is suspicious. For a smaller or starting website a low ranking can be considered normal.\n\nMost companies claim the name of their website (aka domain name) for only one year in advance. they can automatically renew the registration each year. We consider it a positive sign if a domain name is registered for more than one year in the future. It means that the company intends to do business for a long time. We increased the Trust Score of futurenest.com as a result.\n\nThe domain name of this website has been registered several years ago. In general, the older the website the more trustworthy it becomes. However, scammers sometimes buy existing websites and start doing their evil thing, so please make sure you check for other scammy attributes as well.\u00a0\n\n### \n\nTechnical Review\n\nWe identified an SSL certificate meaning that the data shared between your browser and the website is encrypted and cannot be read by others. SSL certificates are always used by legit and safe websites. Last updated: 2024-09-27 10:32:56\n\n## Popular Stories\n\n\u301033\u2020 How to Recognize a Scam Website \u3011 \n\nAs the influence of the internet rises, so does the prevalence of online scams. There are fraudsters making all kinds of claims to trap victims online - from fake investment opportunities to online stores - and the internet allows them to operate from any part of the world with anonymity. The ability to spot online scams is an important skill to have as the virtual world is increasingly becoming a part of every facet of our lives. The below tips will help you identify the signs which can indicate that a website could be a scam. Common Sense: Too Good To Be True When looking for goods online, a great deal can be very enticing. A Gucci bag or a new iPhone for half the price? Who wouldn\u2019t want to grab such a deal? Scammers know this too and try to take advantage of the fact. If an online deal looks too good to be true, think twice and double-check things. The easiest way to do this is to simply check out the same product at competing websites (that you trust). If the difference in prices is huge, it might be better to double-check the rest of the website. Check Out the Social Media Links Social media is a core part of ecommerce businesses these days and consumers often expect online shops to have a social media presence. Scammers know this and often insert logos of social media sites on their websites. Scratching beneath the surface often reveals this fu \n\n\u301033\u2020 Read more \u3011 \n\n\u301034\u2020 How Do I Get Money Back From a Scammer? \u3011 \n\nSo the worst has come to pass - you realise you parted with your money too fast, and the site you used was a scam - what now? Well first of all, don\u2019t despair!! If you think you have been scammed, the first port of call when having an issue is to simply ask for a refund. This is the first and easiest step to determine whether you are dealing with a genuine company or scammers. Sadly, getting your money back from a scammer is not as simple as just asking.\u00a0 If you are indeed dealing with scammers, the procedure (and chance) of getting your money back varies depending on the payment method you used. PayPal Debit card/Credit card Bank transfer Wire transfer Google Pay Bitcoin PayPal If you used PayPal, you have a strong chance of getting your money back if you were scammed. On their website, you can file a dispute within 180 calendar days of your purchase. Conditions to file a dispute: The simplest situation is that you ordered from an online store and it has not arrived. For a smaller or starting website a low ranking can be considered normal.\n\nMost companies claim the name of their website (aka domain name) for only one year in advance. they can automatically renew the registration each year. We consider it a positive sign if a domain name is registered for more than one year in the future. It means that the company intends to do business for a long time. We increased the Trust Score of futurenest.com as a result.\n\nThe domain name of this website has been registered several years ago. There are fraudsters making all kinds of claims to trap victims online - from fake investment opportunities to online stores - and the internet allows them to operate from any part of the world with anonymity. The ability to spot online scams is an important skill to have as the virtual world is increasingly becoming a part of every facet of our lives. The below tips will help you identify the signs which can indicate that a website could be a scam. Common Sense: Too Good To Be True When looking for goods online, a great deal can be very enticing. A Gucci bag or a new iPhone for half the price? Who wouldn\u2019t want to grab such a deal? Scammers know this too and try to take advantage of the fact. If an online deal looks too good to be true, think twice and double-check things. The easiest way to do this is to simply check out the same product at competing websites (that you trust). If the difference in prices is huge, it might be better to double-check the rest of the website. Check Out the Social Media Links Social media is a core part of ecommerce businesses these days and consumers often expect online shops to have a social media presence. Scammers know this and often insert logos of social media sites on their websites. There are fraudsters making all kinds of claims to trap victims online - from fake investment opportunities to online stores - and the internet allows them to operate from any part of the world with anonymity. The ability to spot online scams is an important skill to have as the virtual world is increasingly becoming a part of every facet of our lives. The below tips will help you identify the signs which can indicate that a website could be a scam. Common Sense: Too Good To Be True When looking for goods online, a great deal can be very enticing. A Gucci bag or a new iPhone for half the price? Who wouldn\u2019t want to grab such a deal? Scammers know this too and try to take advantage of the fact. If an online deal looks too good to be true, think twice and double-check things. The easiest way to do this is to simply check out the same product at competing websites (that you trust). If the difference in prices is huge, it might be better to double-check the rest of the website. Check Out the Social Media Links Social media is a core part of ecommerce businesses these days and consumers often expect online shops to have a social media presence. Scammers know this and often insert logos of social media sites on their websites. Scratching beneath the surface often reveals this fu \n\n\u301033\u2020 Read more \u3011 \n\n\u301034\u2020 How Do I Get Money Back From a Scammer? \u3011 \n\nSo the worst has come to pass - you realise you parted with your money too fast, and the site you used was a scam - what now? This is the first and easiest step to determine whether you are dealing with a genuine company or scammers. PayPal Debit card/Credit card Bank transfer Wire transfer Google Pay Bitcoin PayPal If you used PayPal, you have a strong chance of getting your money back if you were scammed. On their website, you can file a dispute within 180 calendar days of your purchase. It&#x27;s that simple.&quot; The scammer has sent you a completely different item. For example, you ordered a PlayStation 4, but instead received only a Playstation controller.\u00a0 The condition of the item was misrepresented on the product page. This can be considered low in relation to other websites from the website&#x27;s country. If you think this website should be very popular, please invest additional time in researching the company as this is suspicious. For a smaller or starting website a low ranking can be considered normal.\n\nMost companies claim the name of their website (aka domain name) for only one year in advance. they can automatically renew the registration each year. We consider it a positive sign if a domain name is registered for more than one year in the future. It means that the company intends to do business for a long time. We increased the Trust Score of futurenest.com as a result.\n\nThe domain name of this website has been registered several years ago. In general, the older the website the more trustworthy it becomes. Last updated: 2024-09-27 10:32:56\n\n## Popular Stories\n\n\u301033\u2020 How to Recognize a Scam Website \u3011 \n\nAs the influence of the internet rises, so does the prevalence of online scams. There are fraudsters making all kinds of claims to trap victims online - from fake investment opportunities to online stores - and the internet allows them to operate from any part of the world with anonymity. The ability to spot online scams is an important skill to have as the virtual world is increasingly becoming a part of every facet of our lives. The below tips will help you identify the signs which can indicate that a website could be a scam. Common Sense: Too Good To Be True When looking for goods online, a great deal can be very enticing. A Gucci bag or a new iPhone for half the price? Who wouldn\u2019t want to grab such a deal? Scammers know this too and try to take advantage of the fact. If an online deal looks too good to be true, think twice and double-check things. The easiest way to do this is to simply check out the same product at competing websites (that you trust). If the difference in prices is huge, it might be better to double-check the rest of the website. Check Out the Social Media Links Social media is a core part of ecommerce businesses these days and consumers often expect online shops to have a social media presence. Scammers know this and often insert logos of social media sites on their websites. Scratching beneath the surface often reveals this fu \n\n\u301033\u2020 Read more \u3011 \n\n\u301034\u2020 How Do I Get Money Back From a Scammer? \u3011 \n\nSo the worst has come to pass - you realise you parted with your money too fast, and the site you used was a scam - what now? Well first of all, don\u2019t despair!! If you think you have been scammed, the first port of call when having an issue is to simply ask for a refund. This is the first and easiest step to determine whether you are dealing with a genuine company or scammers. Sadly, getting your money back from a scammer is not as simple as just asking.\u00a0 If you are indeed dealing with scammers, the procedure (and chance) of getting your money back varies depending on the payment method you used. PayPal Debit card/Credit card Bank transfer Wire transfer Google Pay Bitcoin PayPal If you used PayPal, you have a strong chance of getting your money back if you were scammed. On their website, you can file a dispute within 180 calendar days of your purchase. Conditions to file a dispute: The simplest situation is that you ordered from an online store and it has not arrived. In this case this is what PayPal states: &quot;If your order never shows up and the seller can&#x27;t provide proof of shipment or delivery, you&#x27;ll get a full refund. It&#x27;s that simple.&quot; The scammer has sent you a completely different item. For example, you ordered a PlayStation 4, but instead received only a Playstation controller.\u00a0 The condition of the item was misrepresented on the product page. There are a few approaches to doing this:\n\n### 1. **Referral Programs for Recruiting**\n   Many companies use referral programs to encourage employees or external partners to recommend potential candidates for job openings. These referrals are incentivized by providing rewards, either as cash bonuses, gift cards, or other benefits, once the referred candidate gets hired and completes a probation period. This structure is quite similar to affiliate marketing, as referrers earn commissions for successful &quot;conversions.&quot;\n\n### 2. **Affiliate Recruiting Networks**\n   Some platforms work like affiliate marketing networks but specifically focus on recruiting. These platforms allow people to become &quot;affiliates&quot; by promoting job listings or career opportunities for specific companies. If a candidate applies and gets hired via the affiliate\u2019s referral link, the affiliate earns a commission. Examples of such platforms include:\n   - **Indeed** and **Glassdoor** sometimes allow partner integrations, where traffic or candidates referred from certain partners generate commissions.\n   - **JobTarget** offers a service to distribute job postings across multiple job boards and uses a commission model to encourage partnerships.\n  \n### 3. **Social Recruiting with Affiliate Strategies**\n   Similar to influencer marketing, recruiters or employers can partner with social media influencers who promote job openings to their audience. These influencers may earn a commission or flat fee for each successful candidate they refer. This is especially effective in niche industries where certain influencers have a relevant audience (e.g., tech, creative fields).\n\n### 4. **Platform-Based Recruiting Referral Programs**\n   Platforms like **Workable** and **SmartRecruiters** offer built-in tools for referral recruiting. Companies can share job postings with employees, who in turn can share them with their networks, and receive rewards if those contacts are hired. This turns every employee into an affiliate-like recruiter.\n\n### 5. **Recruitment Marketing Agencies**\n   Agencies that specialize in recruitment marketing can also operate on a performance-based model, similar to affiliate marketing. They help drive candidate applications to employers, and they are paid based on metrics such as the number of successful hires.\n\n### 6. **Freelance Recruiter Platforms**\n   Platforms like **Hiretual** and **Recruitifi** allow freelance recruiters to submit candidates to companies\u2019 open positions. Aim for $0.50 or less if possible.\n   - **Conversion Rate**: A 5%+ conversion rate from the landing page is ideal.\n\n2. **Quick Optimization Steps**:\n   - **Pause Low-Performing Ads**: If any ad set or ad within the first 24 hours has a high CPC, low CTR, or no conversions, pause it to save your budget.\n   - **Reallocate Budget**: Move the saved budget from paused ads to high-performers.\n   - **Refine Audience**: If certain interests perform better, narrow down your audience to those interests only.\n\n### Step 5: Scaling the Campaign After Initial Tests\nAfter identifying the best-performing ad, reinvest into that specific ad set or variation:\n\n1. **Increase Budget on the Winning Ad Set**: Scale it by 20-30% to avoid overspending but boost exposure to the successful audience segment.\n2. **Duplicate for a Fresh Test**: To avoid ad fatigue, duplicate the winning ad set and test a slight variation in the ad copy or image, maintaining the same high-converting audience.\n\nThis structured approach should help you quickly identify top-performing ads, control spending, and reinvest wisely to get faster, optimized returns.
